ty%20worsened%20by%20a%20prolonged%20drought.%20These%20culls%20have%20faced%20criticism%20from%20animal%20rights%20advocates%20and%20conservationists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Farawo%2C%20Zimbabwe's%20elephant%20population%20is%20over%2084%2C000%2C%20nearly%20double%20its%20estimated%20capacity%20of%2045%2C000.%20It%20is%20the%20second%20largest%20globally%20after%20Botswana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Environment%20Minister%20Sithembiso%20Nyoni%20informed%20parliament%20that%20Zimbabwe%20has%20more%20elephants%20than%20needed%20and%20more%20than%20the%20forests%20can%20sustain.%20She%20noted%20that%20elephant%20overpopulation%20leads%20to%20resource%20shortages%2C%20intensifying%20human-wildlife%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENyoni%20added%20that%20the%20government%20is%20considering%20strategies%20similar%20to%20Namibia's%2C%20including%20counting%20the%20elephants%20and%20organizing%20communities%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20to%20preserve%20and%20distribute%20the%20meat%20to%20protein-deficient%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20wildlife%20overpopulates%20a%20park%2C%20they%20venture%20beyond%20it%20in%20search%20of%20resources%20like%20water%20or%20vegetation.%20This%20brings%20them%20into%20contact%20with%20humans%2C%20sparking%20conflicts%2C%26quot%3B%20Nyoni%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Namibia%2C%20the%20government%20authorized%20the%20culling%20of%20700%20wild%20animals%2C%20including%20elephants%2C%20to%20distribute%20to%20people%20facing%20food%20shortages.%20So%20far%2C%20150%20animals%20have%20been%20culled%2C%20and%20over%20125%2C000%20pounds%20of%20meat%20distributed%2C%20according%20to%20Namibia's%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forestry%2C%20and%20Tourism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZimbabwe%20and%20Namibia%20are%20among%20the%20southern%20African%20countries%20enduring%20a%20severe%20drought%20exacerbated%20by%20El%20Nino%20and%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarawo%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Zimbabwe's%20parks%20authority%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20culling%20will%20begin%20once%20the%20required%20documentation%20is%20finalized.%20The%20slaughter%20will%20target%20regions%20with%20dense%20elephant%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20these%20proposed%20elephant%20culls%20have%20faced%20strong%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarai%20Maguwu%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Zimbabwe-based%20Center%20for%20Natural%20Resource%20Governance%2C%20condemned%20the%20practice%20on%20X%2C%20stating%2C%20%26quot%3BCulling%20of%20elephants%20must%20be%20stopped.%20Elephants%20have%20a%20right%20to%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20future%20generations%20deserve%20to%20see%20elephants%20in%20their%20natural%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ECulling%20of%20elephants%20must%20be%20stopped.%20Some%20are%20eying%20an%20opportunity%20to%20sell%20ivory%2C%20illicitly%20-%20what%20with%20these%20private%20jets%20flying%20out%20week%20in%2C%20week%20out.%20With%20the%20way%20minerals%20are%20being%20looted%2C%20soon%20we%20wont%20have%20any%20elephant%20to%20talk%20about.%20Hands%20off%20our%20wildlife!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Farai%20Maguwu%20(%40FMaguwu)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FFMaguwu%2Fstatus%2F1835366038843589062%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2015%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeith%20Lindsay%2C%20a%20conservation%20biologist%20and%20natural%20resources%20consultant%2C%20also%20expressed%20concern%20that%20using%20wildlife%20to%20address%20food%20insecurity%20could%20lead%20to%20unsustainable%20demand%20for%20bushmeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarawo%20defended%20the%20cull%2C%20Zimbabwe's%20first%20since%201988%2C%20as%20part%20of%20broader%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20human-elephant%20conflicts%2C%20following%20a%20string%20of%20fatal%20elephant%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn