0perceiving%20that%20recession%20risks%20were%20rising%20by%20cutting%20more%20than%20most%20economists%20anticipated.%20Instead%2C%20he%20offered%20reassurance%2C%20saying%20the%20Fed's%20patience%20in%20not%20moving%20until%20now%20had%20paid%20%26quot%3Bdividends%26quot%3B%20by%20boosting%20confidence%20inflation%20-%20which%20had%20surged%20to%20the%20highest%20since%20the%201980s%20-%20has%20been%20tamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20move%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20sign%20of%20our%20commitment%20not%20to%20get%20behind%26quot%3B%20the%20curve%2C%20he%20said.%20Investors%20initially%20reacted%20with%20confidence%2C%20though%20US%20stocks%20closed%20with%20modest%20declines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20half-point%20cut%20by%20the%20Fed%20will%20ripple%20through%20other%20central%20banks'%20interest-rate%20decisions%20and%20lead%20market%20participants%20to%20conclude%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20slowing%2C%20perhaps%20leading%20to%20a%20global%20slowdown%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stefan%20Gerlach%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20EFG%20Bank%20in%20Zurich%20and%20a%20former%20deputy%20governor%20of%20the%20central%20bank%20of%20Ireland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20tempt%20the%20European%20Central%20Bank%20to%20consider%20lowering%20rates%20again%20next%20month%2C%20for%20a%20third%20time%20since%20June%2C%20an%20option%20%26quot%3Bit%20has%20firmly%20sought%20to%20push%20back%20against%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerlach%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolicymakers%20led%20by%20President%20Christine%20Lagarde%20are%20going%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20stress%20they%20decide%20on%20policy%20independently.%20In%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20ECB's%20first%20rate%20cut%20in%20June%20-%20when%20the%20US%20economy%20was%20still%20running%20hot%20-%20Lagarde%20insisted%20that%20the%20move%20would%20be%20inspired%20by%20data%2C%20not%20the%20Fed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they've%20also%20acknowledged%20that%20US%20monetary%20policy%20has%20significant%20repercussions%20for%20the%2020-nation%20bloc.%20They%20haven't%20ruled%20out%20lowering%20borrowing%20costs%20in%20October%2C%20even%20if%20such%20a%20move%20is%20unlikely%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20said%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActing%20that%20month%20and%20again%20in%20December%20would%20put%20the%20ECB%20and%20Fed%20eye-to-eye%20on%20the%20overall%20size%20of%20rate%20cuts%20this%20year.%20US%20officials%20expect%20borrowing%20costs%20to%20be%20100%20basis%20points%20lower%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20than%20they%20were%20before%20Wednesday's%20half-point%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20study%20by%20the%20Institute%20of%20International%20Finance%20showed%20rate%20changes%20in%20the%20US%20have%20been%20the%20most%20important%20driver%20of%20decisions%20in%20Europe%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20Roundup%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20the%20ECB%20makes%20decisions%20independently%20from%20the%20Fed%2C%20interest-rate%20differentials%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20Fed%20may%20have%20real%20economic%20effects%20in%20the%20euro%20area%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20should%20be%20taken%20into%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Marcello%20Estevao%2C%20the%20IIF's%20chief%20economist.%20Otherwise%2C%20they'd%20risk%20an%20appreciation%20of%20the%20euro%2C%20declining%20exports%2C%20a%20weaker%20economy%20and%20a%20disinflationary%20shock.%3Cbr%3E%5CnGlobal%20Roundup%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmerging-market%20central%20banks%20in%20countries%20including%20those%20in%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20that%20peg%20their%20currencies%20to%20the%20dollar%20followed%20suit%20and%20also%20lowered%20rates%20by%20half%20a%20point.%20The%20Hong%20Kong%20Monetary%20Authority%20also%20cut%20its%20base%20rate%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Fed's%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThursday%20will%20probably%20see%20the%20Bank%20of%20England%20keeping%20policy%20unchanged%2C%20while%20the%20South%20African%20Reserve%20Bank%20is%20expected%20to%20lower%20its%20rate%20by%20a%20quarter%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20likely%20reaction%20in%20emerging%20markets%20with%20free-floating%20currencies%20isn't%20so%20obvious.%20While%20they%2C%20too%2C%20have%20often%20followed%20the%20Fed%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20US%20central%20bank%20has%20proved%20less%20of%20an%20anchor%20in%20the%20current%20cycle%2C%20according%20to%20Bloomberg%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20disconnect%20backs%20our%20expectation%20that%20emerging%20economies%20will%2C%20on%20net%2C%20ease%20by%20less%20than%20the%20Fed%20in%20the%20year%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloomberg%20Economics's%20Adriana%20Dupita%20and%20Alex%20Isakov%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20Jakarta%20raced%20ahead%20with%20a%20quarter-point%20cut%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20lower%20rates%20in%20the%20US%20frees%20up%20space%20for%20rate%20setters%20from%20Seoul%20to%20Mumbai%20to%20move%20too%2C%20though%20other%20considerations%20like%20financial%20stability%20are%20in%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%20where%20central%20bankers%20are%20just%20getting%20started%20with%20tightening%20policy%2C%20the%20Fed's%20move%20may%20have%20implications%20on%20what's%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bank%20of%20Japan%20is%20widely%20expected%20to%20keep%20interest%20rates%20unchanged%20on%20Friday.%20Updated%20forecasts%20in%20October%20may%20shine%20the%20light%20on%20hotter%20wage%20and%20price%20trends%20and%20tempt%20them%20to%20hike%20by%20a%20quarter-point%2C%20says%20Taro%20Kimura%2C%20BE's%20senior%20Japan%20economist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20unless%20the%20Fed's%20decision%20is%20taken%20as%20a%20warning%20shot%20that%20more%20serious%20trouble%20is%20ahead%20for%20the%20global%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726710960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fcvojsn8g_federal-reserve-us-bloomberg_625x300_19_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com