es%20work%20on%20radio%20waves%20to%20examine%20the%20universe%2C%20it%20makes%20the%20collection%20of%20clean%20data%20much%20more%20complicated%20because%20of%20the%20interference%20caused%20by%20these%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarlink%20satellites%20connect%20remote%20areas%20with%20broadband%20internet%2C%20be%20it%20challenging%20conditions%20like%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Yemen%20or%20the%20rural%20districts%20of%20the%20UK%2C%20for%20that%20matter.%20The%20Department%20for%20Digital%2C%20Culture%2C%20Media%2C%20and%20Sport%20reported%20how%20tests%20conducted%20in%202022%20showed%20that%20Starlink%20could%20deliver%20internet%20speeds%20four%20times%20faster%20than%20the%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FOIqLn152th8%3Fsi%3D4kYTvvqh5rdDXDz6%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20argue%2C%20however%2C%20that%20such%20privilege%20comes%20at%20an%20appreciable%20cost%20in%20terms%20of%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20LOFAR%20(Low%20Frequency%20Array)%2C%20we%20have%20started%20a%20program%20to%20monitor%20unintended%20emission%20from%20satellites%20belonging%20to%20different%20constellations%2C%20and%20our%20observations%20show%20that%20the%20second-generation%20Starlink%20satellites%20emit%20stronger%20emission%20and%20do%20so%20over%20a%20larger%20range%20of%20radio%20frequencies%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20first-generation%20satellites%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.astron.nl%2Fstarlink-satellites%2F%5C%22%3Esays%20Cees%20Bassa%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20ASTRON%20(the%20Netherlands%20Institute%20for%20Radio%20Astronomy)%2C%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.astron.nl%2Fstarlink-satellites%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Erelease%20by%20ASTRON%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20analysis%20revealed%20that%20these%20newer%20satellites%20emit%20up%20to%2032%20times%20brighter%20unintended%20radio%20waves%20compared%20to%20the%20first%20generation%2C%20with%20levels%20potentially%20exceeding%20internationally%20regulated%20thresholds%20for%20interference%20set%20for%20intentional%20emissions%20and%20even%20more%20relaxed%20terrestrial%20electromagnetic%20compatibility%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompared%20to%20the%20faintest%20astrophysical%20sources%20that%20we%20observe%20with%20LOFAR%2C%20UEMR%20from%20Starlink%20satellites%20is%2010%20million%20times%20brighter.%20This%20difference%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20faintest%20stars%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye%20and%20the%20brightness%20of%20the%20full%20moon.%20Since%20SpaceX%20is%20launching%20about%2040%20second-generation%20Starlink%20satellites%20every%20week%2C%20this%20problem%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Cees%20Bassa.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHumanity%20is%20clearly%20approaching%20an%20inflexion%20point%20where%20we%20need%20to%20take%20action%20to%20preserve%20our%20sky%20as%20a%20window%20to%20explore%20the%20universe%20from%20Earth.%20Satellite%20companies%20are%20not%20interested%20in%20producing%20this%20unintended%20radiation%2C%20so%20minimising%20it%20should%20also%20be%20a%20priority%20in%20their%20sustainable%20space%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Federico%20Di%20Vruno%20from%20the%20SKA%20Observatory.%20%26quot%3BStarlink%20is%20not%20the%20only%20big%20player%20in%20LEO%2C%20but%20they%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20set%20the%20standard%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20emphasise%20that%20while%20the%20second-generation%20satellites%20have%20been%20designed%20to%20enhance%20connectivity%20and%20provide%20communication%20services%2C%20the%20unintended%20radio%20emissions%20are%20a%20growing%20threat%20to%20the%20integrity%20of%20astronomical%20observations.%20As%20the%20consequences%20of%20such%20interference%20become%20increasingly%20evident%2C%20collaboration%20between%20satellite%20companies%2C%20regulatory%20agencies%2C%20and%20the%20astronomical%20community%20is%20essential%20to%20devise%20effective%20mitigation%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726672920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F8c9nv46g_elon-musks-starlink-satellites_625x300_18_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Felon-musks-starlink-satellites-blocking-view-of-the-universe-report-6595679%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dutch%20scientists%20from%20ASTRON%20are%20raising%20concerns%20about%20the%20second-generation%20Starlink%20satellites%2C%20claiming%20they%20cause%20significant%20interference%20with%20radio%20telescopes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Felon-musks-starlink-satellites-blocking-view-of-the-universe-report-6595679%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20is%20a%20walkie-talkie%3F%20Device%20linked%20to%20round%202%20of%20fatal%20explosions%20in%20Lebanon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726671758000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113464614%2Cimgsize-623544.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fwhat-is-a-walkie-talkie-device-linked-to-another-fatal-explosions-in-lebanon%2Farticleshow%2F113462710.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F113462710.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20explosions%20linked%20to%20walkie-talkies%20used%20by%20Hezbollah%20struck%20Lebanon's%20southern%20regions%20and%20Beirut's%20suburbs%2C%